</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034CC31BBED281DCFE0F33E5" blockId="4.[189,1399,649,745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="78">
Movable finger of chelicera with three teeth (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034CC31BBCB581DCFCA633AF" box="[730,822,649,675]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,272,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[198,1389,265,1927]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH). A. Chelicera, mesal view. B. Chelicera, frontal view. C. Pedipalpal femur, mesal view. D. Pedipalpal tibia and tarsus, ventral view." pageId="4" pageNumber="78">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
), small and wide. Tubercles of leg IV small and scattered; patella with few, small tubercles (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034CC31BBCA781F9FCB633CA" box="[712,806,684,710]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1162,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-156@4.[189,1398,1162,1927]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH). A. Apical femur, patella and basal tibia IV. B. Patella IV." pageId="4" pageNumber="78">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Penis with one pair of MS D, MS E1 below the level of E2 (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034CC31BBF20819AFE1F33E5" box="[335,399,719,745]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1251,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-283@5.[189,1398,1251,1921]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH), penis. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Scale bar in C applicable to all figures." pageId="4" pageNumber="78">Fig 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
