<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034DC31ABED28751FCD33512" blockId="5.[189,835,993,1054]" box="[189,835,1028,1054]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">MEASUREMENTS. Scutum length: 4.9, scutum width: 4.1.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034DC31ABED28710FAE6358F" blockId="5.[189,1399,1093,1155]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">
CHELICERA (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034DC31ABF258710FE1F3553" box="[330,399,1093,1119]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,272,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[198,1389,265,1927]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH). A. Chelicera, mesal view. B. Chelicera, frontal view. C. Pedipalpal femur, mesal view. D. Pedipalpal tibia and tarsus, ventral view." pageId="5" pageNumber="79">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B). Scutum/cheliceral hand ratio: 1.37. Basichelicerite long, with diffuse bulla. Cheliceral hand slightly swollen, fixed finger with six teeth distributed evenly throughout, middle one
</paragraph>
<caption id="89EB667E034DC31ABED284FEFB9C36E4" pageId="5" pageNumber="79" startId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" targetBox="[189,1398,1251,1921]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034DC31ABED284FEFB9C36E4" blockId="5.[189,1399,1963,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis id="EFE0EAE4034DC31ABED284FEFE9E36C9" bold="true" box="[189,270,1963,1989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1A944D75034DC31ABF7584FEFCAC36C9" authority="Silhavy, 1974" authorityName="Silhavy" authorityYear="1974" box="[282,828,1963,1992]" class="Arachnida" family="Stygnopsidae" genus="Troglostygnopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anophthalma">
<emphasis id="EFE0EAE4034DC31ABF7584FEFD1736C9" box="[282,647,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">Troglostygnopsis anophthalma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B9054B07034DC31ABCFD84F9FCAC36C9" author="Silhavy V." box="[658,828,1963,1992]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79" pagination="175 - 194" refId="ref6023" refString="Silhavy V. 1974. Cavernicolous opilionids from Mexico. Subterranean fauna of Mexico. Part. II. Quaderno Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei 171: 175 - 194." type="journal article" year="1974">Šilhavý, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH), penis. 
<emphasis id="EFE0EAE4034DC31ABAD884FEFB5C36C9" bold="true" box="[1207,1228,1963,1989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">A</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="EFE0EAE4034DC31ABED2849BFF4136E4" bold="true" box="[189,209,1998,2024]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">B</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis id="EFE0EAE4034DC31ABF10849BFE0436E4" bold="true" box="[383,404,1998,2024]" pageId="5" pageNumber="79">C</emphasis>
. Ventral view. Scale bar in C applicable to all figures.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034EC319BED2825CFED8304A" blockId="6.[189,1399,265,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="80">biggest; movable finger with three scattered teeth, basalmost and middle ones small and triangular, distal one diffuse.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034EC319BED2823BFC723373" blockId="6.[188,1400,365,639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="80">
PEDIPALPS (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034EC319BF29823BFE013084" box="[326,401,366,392]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,272,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[198,1389,265,1927]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH). A. Chelicera, mesal view. B. Chelicera, frontal view. C. Pedipalpal femur, mesal view. D. Pedipalpal tibia and tarsus, ventral view." pageId="6" pageNumber="80">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C–D). Measurements: 2.30/1.00/1.75/1.80/1.00. Trochanter globose, with three ventral spiniform tubercles, apical one very large, dorsally with one spiniform tubercle. Femur slightly compressed laterally, with one ventral and one dorsal row of large spiniform tubercles pointing distally, these tubercles uniformly distributed throughout femur, ventral basalmost one most prominent. Patella with few small spiniform tubercles. Tibia with long armature, with relative sizes of three major tubercles (SST) on mesal side 1 = 3&gt; 2, and on ectal margin 3 = 2&gt; 1, on this segment two small setiferous tubercles between SST 1 and 2, and at apical end of the margin. Tarsus with six major tubercles on mesal side (2&gt; 4 = 5&gt; 6&gt; 1 = 3) and five on ectal side (1&gt; 4&gt; 2 = 3 = 5).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034EC319BED281F3FE3B320A" blockId="6.[189,1398,677,774]" pageId="6" pageNumber="80">
LEGS (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034EC319BF6681F0FEC533CC" box="[265,341,677,704]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1162,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-156@4.[189,1398,1162,1927]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH). A. Apical femur, patella and basal tibia IV. B. Patella IV." pageId="6" pageNumber="80">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). All segments very long and slender, femur IV longer than scutum. Ornamentation of femur IV composed of small and scattered tubercles forming longitudinal rows, patella covered with few small tubercles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034EC319BED2807BFABA32D8" blockId="6.[189,1401,813,981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="80">
PENIS (
<figureCitation id="45AF2A73034EC319BF628078FEC6324B" box="[269,342,813,839]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1251,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-283@5.[189,1398,1251,1921]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Troglostygnopsis anophthalma Šilhavý, 1974, Ƌ, topotype (AMNH), penis. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Scale bar in C applicable to all figures." pageId="6" pageNumber="80">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Pars distalis with an apical concavity, lateral and apical margins softly rolled dorsally. Follis rugose, apices of dorsal bilobular projection long and pointed. One pair of small MS D lateral to base of follis, near to lateral margins of pars distalis. Four pairs of acute MS C forming two irregular rows on lateral sides. MS A+B formed by many spatulate setae, on latero-basal portion of pars distalis, some of them on ventral side. MS E composed of two pairs, MS E1 markedly below level of E2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2B36F6034EC319BE8580A9FEFA3535" blockId="6.[189,362,1020,1081]" pageId="6" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis id="EFE0EAE4034EC319BE8580A9FED5351A" bold="true" box="[234,325,1020,1046]" pageId="6" pageNumber="80">Female</emphasis>
Not examined.
</paragraph>
